author: ghudson
msg: Because our working copy code can't represent a delete-and-replace
of a directory, the fs-abstraction branch merge will have to happen
in three commits.  This commit moves subversion/tests/libsvn_fs to
subversion/tests/libsvn_fs_base.

author: ghudson
msg: On the fs-abstraction branch, take a change from Chris Foote to
allow BDB repositories to work on Windows with the FS abstraction
code.  (Commits in FSFS directories seem to run avoid of a tree
deletion problem.)
* svn_private_config.hw: Define symbols to link in FS modules.

author: ghudson
msg: Increase the default HTTP timeout to 3600 seconds from the neon
default of 120 seconds.
* libsvn_ra_dav/session.c
(DEFAULT_HTTP_TIMEOUT): New constant for our default HTTP timeout.
(svn_ra_dav__open): If no timeout specified, use our default instead
of Neon's.

author: sussman
msg: Issue #1093:  remove crufty old piece of logic, a likely bug source.
* libsvn_client/ra.c
(svn_client__repos_locations): only one field in the lrb baton can
have a path pre-emptively filled in, and the new code is already
doing this.  Remove this old statement.
